28
00:03:30,820 --> 00:03:33,820
{\pos(196,180)}纸牌屋

29
00:03:30,820 --> 00:03:33,820
{\an2}{\pos(208.1,242.25)}第六季  第四集

30
00:03:45,980 --> 00:03:47,180
他找过你了吗
Has he approached you?

31
00:03:49,010 --> 00:03:50,030
谁
Who?

32
00:03:51,040 --> 00:03:52,110
佩特罗夫
Petrov.

33
00:03:55,040 --> 00:03:56,890
他不是刚到吗
Didn't he just arrive?

34
00:03:58,390 --> 00:04:00,870
叙利亚问题的谈判破裂了  他来干什么
If the talks on Syria have broken down, what's he doing here?

35
00:04:01,760 --> 00:04:03,620
不是好事就是坏事
It's either a good thing or a bad thing.

36
00:04:05,310 --> 00:04:06,620
那是好是坏
Well, which is it?

37
00:04:08,800 --> 00:04:09,820
总统女士
Madam President?

38
00:04:11,510 --> 00:04:13,220
他喜欢凯茜
He was fond of Cathy.

39
00:04:20,320 --> 00:04:23,350
我需要知道  你不会妨碍我处理...
I need to know that you won't stand in the way of my handling...

40
00:04:23,350 --> 00:04:25,880
马克  结束了
Mark. It's done.

41
00:04:27,200 --> 00:04:28,210
你赢了
You won.

42
00:04:34,660 --> 00:04:36,430
给你看是必要的
It was necessary to show you,

43
00:04:37,420 --> 00:04:38,670
但我并不想这样
but not what I wanted.

44
00:04:38,670 --> 00:04:40,270
我不知道你在说什么
I don't know what you're talking about.

45
00:04:41,980 --> 00:04:44,440
你害了我也害了自己  这得怪你
You did that to both of us. You did it.

46
00:04:45,610 --> 00:04:48,340
你把我卷进来  害我有牵连
You involved me, you implicated me.

47
00:04:50,910 --> 00:04:53,090
-你把他丢在我房子里  -马克  够了
- You left him in my house. - Mark, that's enough.

48
00:04:54,740 --> 00:04:56,110
都不重要了
It doesn't matter anymore.

49
00:05:08,220 --> 00:05:10,570
斯坦  请节哀顺变
Stan, my deepest condolences.

50
00:05:10,980 --> 00:05:15,460
这是凯茜的弟弟亨特  从尤金赶过来的
This is Cathy's brother Hunter. He flew in from Eugene.

51
00:05:15,820 --> 00:05:18,150
就在莱恩县外
Just outside Lane County.

52
00:05:18,330 --> 00:05:19,920
那里的乡景很美
Beautiful country out there.

53
00:05:21,260 --> 00:05:23,530
我本来也打算出来走走
I was planning to come out anyway.

54
00:05:24,590 --> 00:05:26,390
六号就是斯坦的生日了
Stan's birthday is on the sixth.

55
00:05:26,390 --> 00:05:27,740
凯茜和我
Cathy and I have been...

56
00:05:28,240 --> 00:05:29,930
忙活了几个月了
back and forth for months.

57
00:05:29,970 --> 00:05:31,740
您丧失至亲  我非常难过
I'm so sorry for your loss.

58
00:05:32,950 --> 00:05:36,450
道格  这位是凯茜的弟弟亨特
Doug, this is Cathy's brother Hunter.

59
00:05:37,090 --> 00:05:38,190
你认识斯坦
And you've met Stan.

60
00:05:38,190 --> 00:05:40,180
-当然  -谢谢你过来
- Of course. - Thank you for coming.

61
00:05:40,840 --> 00:05:44,640
我想道格大概是与凯茜相处最久的了
Doug, I think, spent more time with Cathy than anyone.

62
00:05:45,830 --> 00:05:47,070
真是太可惜了
She didn't deserve this.

63
00:05:48,150 --> 00:05:49,910
说实话  我都觉得有些不真实
Honestly, it doesn't seem real.

64
00:05:54,220 --> 00:05:55,380
失陪一下好吗
Would you excuse me?

65
00:05:58,130 --> 00:05:59,360
她什么时候过世的
What time did she die?

66
00:06:00,950 --> 00:06:02,000
我不...
I don't...

67
00:06:02,620 --> 00:06:04,900
抱歉  我知道这么问不合适  我只是
Sorry, I know it's a weird question. I just...

68
00:06:04,910 --> 00:06:06,680
我那天突然有所感应
I had one of those feelings that day.

69
00:06:09,730 --> 00:06:12,110
5点43分吧
5:43, I think.

70
00:06:12,310 --> 00:06:14,730
是啊  差不多就是那时候
Yeah, right around then.

71
00:06:17,040 --> 00:06:18,220
总统先生
Mr. President.

72
00:06:18,500 --> 00:06:20,130
安德伍德总统
President Underwood.

73
00:06:21,350 --> 00:06:24,480
杜兰特国务卿是来自上一个时代的人
Secretary Durant was from a time that's passed.

74
00:06:24,690 --> 00:06:26,250
{\an1}{\pos(4,247)}克林顿政府驻联合国大使
奥巴马政府驻中东特使

75
00:06:24,690 --> 00:06:26,250
{\an3}{\pos(374,247)}克林顿政府国务卿

76
00:06:24,690 --> 00:06:26,250
霍尔布鲁克  奥尔布赖特
Holbrooke, Albright...

77
00:06:26,260 --> 00:06:29,060
他们知道先觥筹交错  推杯换盏一番
They knew how to have a good meal and some friendly conversation

78
00:06:29,060 --> 00:06:30,990
再去厮杀那些外交问题
before diplomacy got ugly.

79
00:06:32,510 --> 00:06:34,580
失去了她  确实是不复当年了
It certainly won't be the same without her.

80
00:06:35,590 --> 00:06:38,130
我听说他们把你拴得很紧
I hear they have you on a short leash.

81
00:06:38,880 --> 00:06:41,490
你怎么能容忍这种事呢  总统女士
How could you let that happen, Madam President?

82
00:06:41,740 --> 00:06:45,620
如今危机又近在眼前
Now, when we're only moments away from crisis.

83
00:06:47,790 --> 00:06:49,660
在某些文化中
You know, in some cultures

84
00:06:49,690 --> 00:06:53,030
人们还会真正纪念死者
it occurs to them to actually honor the dead.

85
00:06:54,570 --> 00:06:56,880
马达加斯加人每过七年
Every seven years the Malagasy people

86
00:06:56,880 --> 00:06:59,240
会挖出遗骨  裹上衣服
exhume the bones, wrapping them in cloth,

87
00:06:59,240 --> 00:07:01,510
然后和它们一起跳舞
so they can dance with the bodies.

88
00:07:03,710 --> 00:07:06,210
这座城市又是如何面对的呢
How does this town rise to the occasion?

89
00:07:07,880 --> 00:07:10,410
他们的脑袋下面就跟有弹簧似的
It's like their heads are on a swivel.

90
00:07:12,250 --> 00:07:15,210
那东西叫什么来着
Yeah. What do you call those things?

91
00:07:15,290 --> 00:07:16,500
摇头娃娃
Bobble heads?

92
00:07:17,810 --> 00:07:18,920
太可怕了
Terrifying.

93
00:07:20,260 --> 00:07:21,640
不  别去  随她去吧
No, don't... Let her be.

94
00:07:25,140 --> 00:07:27,190
是你想让她有总统的样儿
You wanted her to play the part.

95
00:07:28,100 --> 00:07:29,210
看吧
Voilà.

96
00:07:29,960 --> 00:07:32,300
-这不是了吗  -总统太好说话了
- The President. - the President is too agreeable.

97
00:07:33,760 --> 00:07:35,030
你对她做了什么
What did you do to her?

98
00:07:35,030 --> 00:07:38,350
比起现在这一套  我更相信她的轻蔑
I trust her contempt more than whatever this is.

99
00:07:38,350 --> 00:07:40,370
亲爱的  我知道你的能耐
Love, I know what you're capable of.

100
00:07:43,890 --> 00:07:47,270
国防情报局认为有超过十万名俄军士兵
DIA believes there are over 100,000 Russian troops

101
00:07:47,270 --> 00:07:49,600
-正在向边境进军  -你联系布加耶夫了吗
- on their way to the border. - Did you find Bugayev?

102
00:07:50,020 --> 00:07:52,380
几分钟之前  他的副手向我保证
As of a few minutes ago, his second in command assured me

103
00:07:52,380 --> 00:07:53,630
克里姆林宫
that was the last contact

104
00:07:53,630 --> 00:07:55,470
将不会再与我们联系
we would have from anyone at the Kremlin.

105
00:07:56,430 --> 00:07:57,600
除了他
Except for him.

106
00:07:59,030 --> 00:08:01,500
他请求和总统进行私下会晤
He's requesting a private meeting with the President.

107
00:08:01,510 --> 00:08:03,650
-好啊  -该死的
- Sure. - God damn it.

108
00:08:04,330 --> 00:08:06,740
-总统先生  -副总统先生
- Mr. President. - Mr. Vice President.

109
00:08:07,160 --> 00:08:08,520
您见过西格森国务卿
You know Secretary Siegerson.

110
00:08:08,520 --> 00:08:10,080
-当然  -见到您很高兴
- Yes. Of course. - So good to see you.

111
00:08:11,480 --> 00:08:13,630
总统女士  打扰一下
Madam President, excuse me.

112
00:08:14,280 --> 00:08:16,300
好的  失陪一下
Oh, yes. Excuse me a moment.

113
00:08:16,300 --> 00:08:17,290
当然
Of course.

114
00:08:19,210 --> 00:08:21,100
凯茜对我很好
Cathy was kind to me.

115
00:08:21,240 --> 00:08:24,110
她是大家的榜样  通情达理  精于业务
A role model. Sensible, shrewd.

116
00:08:24,300 --> 00:08:25,620
法语很流利
Fluent in French.

117
00:08:26,500 --> 00:08:27,750
愿她安息
Repose en paix.

118
00:08:29,740 --> 00:08:31,580
我知道现在说不合适  但是
I know it's not the place, but...

119
00:08:32,750 --> 00:08:34,890
眼下的情况太不正常了
this isn't normal, what's going on.

120
00:08:35,540 --> 00:08:37,010
我接受这个职位的时候
When I accepted my position,

121
00:08:37,010 --> 00:08:38,820
是为了协助您推进您的计划
it was to work with you and your agenda,

122
00:08:38,820 --> 00:08:39,610
而不是
not...

123
00:08:40,430 --> 00:08:41,390
而不是
not...

124
00:08:44,460 --> 00:08:46,550
本届内阁的某些
Certain members of our Cabinet

125
00:08:46,550 --> 00:08:48,830
与国安部事务有关的人
in positions related to National Security

126
00:08:48,830 --> 00:08:51,570
已经就叙利亚问题进行了多次密会
have had several secret meetings regarding Syria.

127
00:08:51,830 --> 00:08:53,500
佩特罗夫总统已经知道
President Petrov has become aware

128
00:08:53,500 --> 00:08:56,940
他们计划排遣雇佣兵进入该地区的事
of their plans for sending private contractors to the region.

129
00:08:57,330 --> 00:08:58,310
女士
Ma'am...

130
00:08:59,220 --> 00:09:01,110
五角大楼一些高层
there are officials in the Pentagon,

131
00:09:01,110 --> 00:09:03,500
克里姆林宫里也有人非常希望能避免一场
people at the Kremlin, who would very much like to prevent

132
00:09:03,500 --> 00:09:06,360
-代理人战争  -诺拉  谢谢你的坦诚
- a proxy war... - Nora, I appreciate your candor,

133
00:09:06,810 --> 00:09:08,170
但马克会处理的
but Mark has this.

134
00:09:08,290 --> 00:09:10,200
女士  内阁都成了他的了
Ma'am, the Cabinet is his.

135
00:09:10,200 --> 00:09:11,610
他知道我们该怎么做
He knows what we need to do.

136
00:09:15,420 --> 00:09:18,770
我之所以怀疑你想竞争议长  是因为
What makes me suspect you're vying for speaker is

137
00:09:19,100 --> 00:09:20,590
尽管领跑选手天天换
the frontrunners change day to day,

138
00:09:20,600 --> 00:09:23,340
但是大家心中的次选始终没变过
but everybody's second choice remains the same.

139
00:09:23,400 --> 00:09:25,210
-就是你  -布雷特  难道你会让贤
- You. - Brett, are you saying you wouldn't do it,

140
00:09:25,220 --> 00:09:26,300
拒绝党内征召吗
if the party asked?

141
00:09:26,480 --> 00:09:28,400
这说明党还没昏了头  分得清好坏
If the party knew what was good for them.

142
00:09:28,530 --> 00:09:32,100
这位是道格拉斯·斯坦普  他现在是顾问
This is Douglas Stamper. He's coming on as a consultant.

143
00:09:32,120 --> 00:09:33,180
大家都认识
We've met.

144
00:09:33,340 --> 00:09:34,890
弗兰西斯当党鞭时认识的约拿
Jonah, back when Francis was whip,

145
00:09:34,890 --> 00:09:38,030
而你  当年还只是端咖啡的小厮
and you, back when you were getting us coffee.

146
00:09:38,310 --> 00:09:40,020
我倒确实想知道  议员先生
I do wonder how he'd feel with some

147
00:09:40,020 --> 00:09:44,130
对他署名的一些法案到底有什么看法
of the legislation the good congressman is putting his name on.

148
00:09:44,450 --> 00:09:46,490
三权分立是宪法之本
Constitution was built on checks and balances.

149
00:09:46,490 --> 00:09:47,700
还有人民的意愿
And the people's will.

150
00:09:48,730 --> 00:09:50,470
总统是谁并不重要
It's not about who the President is.

151
00:09:50,640 --> 00:09:52,360
重要的是政府变成了什么样
It's about what the office has become.

152
00:09:55,220 --> 00:09:57,150
先生们  容我失陪一下
Gentlemen, if you'll excuse me for a minute,

153
00:09:57,150 --> 00:10:00,440
我答应了布雷特介绍些温和派民主党议员给他认识
I promised Brett here I'd introduce him to a blue dog Democrat,

154
00:10:00,510 --> 00:10:01,900
如果我找得到的话
assuming I can find one.

155
00:10:04,040 --> 00:10:05,620
没想到还能再见到他
I never thought I'd see him again.

156
00:10:05,640 --> 00:10:06,820
他去复健了
He was in rehab.

157
00:10:07,750 --> 00:10:09,170
又开始戒酒了
And is back in the program.

158
00:10:09,470 --> 00:10:10,940
那些指控都撤销了
Those charges were dropped,

159
00:10:11,240 --> 00:10:13,100
但还有一桩案子追着他呢
but he's still got a case chasing him.

160
00:10:13,100 --> 00:10:16,630
要我猜  那案子怕是冲着总统去的
If anything, my bet is that case is chasing the President.

161
00:10:16,750 --> 00:10:18,600
佩特罗夫离开大厅了
Petrov is no longer in the main room.

162
00:10:18,680 --> 00:10:20,530
西格森国务卿还和戴维斯女士在一起
Secretary Siegerson is still with Ms. Davis,

163
00:10:21,440 --> 00:10:23,210
副总统正要出去
while the vice president's exiting.

164
00:10:23,620 --> 00:10:25,320
国土安全部部长的卡弗蒂
And Homeland Secretary Cafferty

165
00:10:25,320 --> 00:10:27,520
刚和总统密语了好一阵子
was just whispering with the President.

166
00:10:28,510 --> 00:10:32,330
而道格·斯坦普在和助理局长格林说话
As for Doug Stamper, he's with Assistant Director Green.

167
00:10:36,600 --> 00:10:38,320
我想知道当时谁和杜兰特在一起
I want to know who Durant was with,

168
00:10:38,820 --> 00:10:41,760
什么时间去了哪  直到她被宣布死亡
when and where, leading up to the moment she was pronounced dead.

169
00:10:41,980 --> 00:10:43,640
如果我去打听的话
If I start asking around...

170
00:10:44,410 --> 00:10:46,570
只会问来更多问题
Questions bring more questions.

171
00:10:46,860 --> 00:10:48,940
-这是公开调查吗  -不是
- Is this an open investigation? - No.

172
00:10:49,450 --> 00:10:52,830
不过我会提醒着点和我共事的探员
But for any agent I work with, I'll be the red flag.

173
00:10:53,610 --> 00:10:57,670
道格  我知道得越多  对你我就越有利
Doug, the more I know, the better it is for both of us.

174
00:10:58,850 --> 00:10:59,940
你相信我吗
You trust me?

175
00:11:03,540 --> 00:11:05,140
你总是坚持到底
You've always followed through.

176
00:11:06,590 --> 00:11:07,870
那就听我的
Then do as I say.

177
00:11:15,100 --> 00:11:16,510
你发现了什么
But what did you find?

178
00:11:18,590 --> 00:11:19,740
他招了吗
Is he talking?

179
00:11:21,740 --> 00:11:24,060
好的  有什么新情况就向我汇报
All right. Get back to me when you know anything more.

180
00:11:24,130 --> 00:11:25,190
无论什么时候
Day or night.

181
00:11:28,590 --> 00:11:29,710
有什么事吗
Is everything okay?

182
00:11:30,420 --> 00:11:32,120
是关于汤姆·耶茨的
That was about Tom Yates.

183
00:11:32,280 --> 00:11:34,520
他的信用卡最近发生了一笔消费
There's been a recent charge on his credit card.

184
00:11:34,880 --> 00:11:36,470
就在布拉格的马克大酒店
The Grand Mark in Prague,

185
00:11:36,470 --> 00:11:38,470
只不过并不是汤姆
except it wasn't Tom.

186
00:11:38,470 --> 00:11:41,450
他没进行那笔消费  其他的也不是他
He didn't make the charge. Or any of the others.

187
00:11:41,740 --> 00:11:43,740
-有人偷了他的  -他的身份
- Somebody stole his... - His identity.

188
00:11:45,010 --> 00:11:48,780
我们现在不知道真正的汤姆·耶茨去了哪
As of now, we have no idea where the real Tom Yates has been.

189
00:11:51,090 --> 00:11:52,500
但愿他没事
Well, I hope he's safe.

190
00:11:52,930 --> 00:11:54,160
不管他在哪
Wherever he is.

191
00:11:55,240 --> 00:11:56,270
我也是
Me too.

192
00:12:13,390 --> 00:12:16,850
1945年产的木桐·罗斯柴尔德
1945 Mouton-Rothschild.

193
00:12:17,820 --> 00:12:19,210
V标
"V" Label.

194
00:12:22,580 --> 00:12:26,570
罗斯柴尔德订了这瓶酒  来庆祝盟军
Rothschild commissioned it to celebrate the Allied victory

195
00:12:26,570 --> 00:12:28,490
在伟大卫国战争中的胜利
in the Great Patriotic War.

196
00:12:29,130 --> 00:12:30,520
你是指第二次世界大战
You mean World War II.

197
00:12:33,070 --> 00:12:35,430
不知道她是想留着庆祝什么
I wonder what she was saving this for.

198
00:12:39,310 --> 00:12:40,210
要不要尝尝
Should we?

199
00:12:43,860 --> 00:12:47,270
拜托  你心底里总还有点玩心吧
Come on. There must be some mischief in you somewhere.

200
00:12:48,550 --> 00:12:49,610
你反对吗
Do you object?

201
00:12:51,360 --> 00:12:52,460
我没资格
Not my place.

202
00:12:53,530 --> 00:12:55,600
那你有什么资格
And where exactly is your place?

203
00:12:56,710 --> 00:12:59,620
我明确要求和你们总统会面
I specifically asked to meet with the President.

204
00:13:06,440 --> 00:13:08,770
这里肯定有个开瓶器吧
There must be a corkscrew somewhere, hmm?

205
00:13:09,070 --> 00:13:11,380
她藏了这么多酒  怎么可能没有开瓶器呢
She wouldn't keep these bottles in here without one.

206
00:13:11,730 --> 00:13:14,910
-说到叙利亚  总统先生  -请先等等
- When it comes to Syria, Mr. President... - A moment, please.

207
00:13:17,130 --> 00:13:18,130
先生
Sir...

208
00:13:18,990 --> 00:13:21,210
我们唯一的目标就是保持稳定
our only goal is stability,

209
00:13:21,780 --> 00:13:23,960
为叙利亚人民谋求和平  繁荣
peace, prosperity for the Syrian people.

210
00:13:24,940 --> 00:13:27,530
我们得重新接触  重开谈判
We need to re-engage. We need to re-start talks...

211
00:13:27,530 --> 00:13:28,520
谈判
Talks?

212
00:13:28,820 --> 00:13:30,020
就知道谈
Talk, talk, talk.

213
00:13:30,450 --> 00:13:33,030
然后一转脸就去和奈克西斯幕后交易
While you're busy making side deals with Nexis

214
00:13:33,030 --> 00:13:35,210
还有你们那群共和党朋友
and the rest of your Republican friends.

215
00:13:35,240 --> 00:13:36,340
谢泼德家族
The Shepherds.

216
00:13:36,620 --> 00:13:39,620
他们才是你的主子  是不是
That is who you really work for, isn't it?

217
00:13:40,800 --> 00:13:42,520
我们可以冻结资产
We can freeze assets,

218
00:13:43,510 --> 00:13:46,290
重新启动制裁
put sanctions back into place.

219
00:13:50,620 --> 00:13:52,210
这会儿
Must be about...

220
00:13:52,900 --> 00:13:55,720
大马士革是晚上七点半
7:30 at night in Damascus.

221
00:13:56,870 --> 00:13:58,260
如果我们无所作为
If we do nothing,

222
00:13:58,940 --> 00:14:02,460
到天亮  我们两军的遭遇战就会开始
by dawn, skirmishes between our troops and yours will begin.

223
00:14:02,510 --> 00:14:05,800
等到俄军打死几个你们美军士兵
And once Russian soldiers start killing American soldiers,

224
00:14:07,090 --> 00:14:08,940
乱局就会继续扩大
the chaos will continue.

225
00:14:10,620 --> 00:14:11,600
或者
Or...

226
00:14:12,940 --> 00:14:17,940
我们现在就铺开叙利亚地图
we can pull out a map of Syria, right here, right now.

227
00:14:18,480 --> 00:14:22,200
而你和我  亮出帝国主义者的本色
And you and I, like the imperialists we are,

228
00:14:22,630 --> 00:14:24,960
瓜分各自的利益吧
can decide who gets what.

229
00:14:28,030 --> 00:14:29,020
好吗
Shall we?

230
00:14:30,760 --> 00:14:32,120
我去和总统谈谈
I'll speak to the President.

231
00:14:36,930 --> 00:14:38,670
谁能拍板
Whoever decides...

232
00:14:39,910 --> 00:14:41,810
你就找谁说去吧
is who you should speak to.

233
00:14:49,010 --> 00:14:50,210
真是可惜
What a shame.

234
00:14:56,260 --> 00:14:57,420
太可惜了
What a shame.

235
00:15:22,540 --> 00:15:25,590
我和道格谈过了  他问了我
I talked to Doug. He asked me,

236
00:15:26,010 --> 00:15:27,950
一开始我还以为他是想掩盖
and at first I thought he was just covering his tracks,

237
00:15:27,960 --> 00:15:29,980
他与国务卿之死的瓜葛  但是
as far as the Secretary's death, but...

238
00:15:30,620 --> 00:15:31,750
现在我也不知道
Now I wonder...

239
00:15:33,010 --> 00:15:34,620
他的问题是何用意了
the nature of his questions.

240
00:15:35,240 --> 00:15:37,020
女士  我打了几个电话
Ma'am, I've made some calls.

241
00:15:37,500 --> 00:15:39,100
有些细节对不上
There are some inconsistencies.

242
00:15:39,100 --> 00:15:41,170
她离家的时间  死亡的地点
When she left her house. Where she died.

243
00:15:41,170 --> 00:15:43,210
-等等  什么意思  -我并不是说是假的
- Wait, what are you telling me? - I'm not saying it isn't true...

244
00:15:43,210 --> 00:15:44,270
你等等  慢点说
Just a second, back up.

245
00:15:44,270 --> 00:15:46,030
我只是说还很难确定
It's just hard to be certain is all I'm saying.

246
00:15:50,310 --> 00:15:53,560
-我要你去找到他  -我不能再和他说话了
- I'd like you to go find him. - I can't talk to him again.

247
00:15:56,450 --> 00:15:58,570
我是担心他会起疑
My fear is he'll become suspicious.

248
00:15:59,520 --> 00:16:01,420
他知道我一向听话
He knows me as someone who does what he's told.

249
00:16:01,420 --> 00:16:03,750
我不明白  如果不是他  那么
I don't understand, If it's not him, then...

250
00:16:04,950 --> 00:16:06,790
她到底是怎么死的
how did she die, for God's sake?

251
00:16:08,250 --> 00:16:09,160
女士
Ma'am...

252
00:16:10,250 --> 00:16:11,290
我也不知道
I don't know.

253
00:16:22,660 --> 00:16:25,660
谢泼德先生希望你随时汇报最新情况
Mr. Shepherd would like to be kept informed in real time.

254
00:16:25,940 --> 00:16:27,040
我都有数
It's under control.

255
00:16:27,180 --> 00:16:29,290
那你就更应该跟我们通气了
Then it shouldn't be a problem to keep us included.

256
00:16:29,880 --> 00:16:32,080
你知道我认识谢泼德家多少年了吗
Do you understand how long I've known the Shepherds?

257
00:16:32,660 --> 00:16:35,850
不管你和佩特罗夫谈什么  都得要他点头
Whatever you discussed with Petrov needs to be run by him.

258
00:16:35,850 --> 00:16:37,900
我给你上一课  格雷森先生
Let me enlighten you about something, Mr. Grayson.

259
00:16:38,160 --> 00:16:39,530
我和比尔·谢泼德
I do not need you to convey

260
00:16:39,530 --> 00:16:41,540
用不着你在中间传话  明白了吗
a message between me and Bill Shepherd, okay?

261
00:16:41,540 --> 00:16:44,120
那更好  只要您  请原谅我唐突
Well, that's preferable, as long as, and forgive me,

262
00:16:44,120 --> 00:16:47,680
不背着他擅自决定叙利亚的事
you make no decisions when it comes to Syria without his say-so.

263
00:16:47,680 --> 00:16:50,130
-步子别迈得太大  先生  -到此为止
- Don't get over your skis, sir. - We're done here.

264
00:16:50,220 --> 00:16:52,400
-我不认为  -副总统说了  到此为止
- I don't think... - The vice president says we are done.

265
00:16:58,120 --> 00:16:59,520
道格·斯坦普
Doug Stamper.

266
00:17:02,740 --> 00:17:04,930
琳达  你还好吗
Linda. How are you?

267
00:17:06,100 --> 00:17:08,220
-葬礼你没去  -我去迟了
- You weren't at the funeral. - I arrived late.

268
00:17:09,210 --> 00:17:10,910
退出政坛了吧
Out of politics, I understand?

269
00:17:10,910 --> 00:17:13,570
沃克总统给我安排了很好的去处
President Walker made sure I had a soft landing.

270
00:17:13,570 --> 00:17:15,880
我现在在科罗拉多一所大学
I'm at a university in Colorado,

271
00:17:16,060 --> 00:17:19,460
是个山清水秀的好地方
where the water is fresh and the air is clean.

272
00:17:20,440 --> 00:17:22,370
-听起来很危险  -没错
- Sounds dangerous. - It is.

273
00:17:22,370 --> 00:17:24,200
让你头脑太清醒
To think that clearly.

274
00:17:24,800 --> 00:17:25,820
你还好吗
How are you?

275
00:17:26,970 --> 00:17:28,060
你看过什么了
What have you read?

276
00:17:28,530 --> 00:17:29,640
关于你的吗
About you?

277
00:17:30,400 --> 00:17:31,530
差不多都看了
Most of it.

278
00:17:31,960 --> 00:17:33,750
至少过去三个月的
The last three months of it.

279
00:17:34,990 --> 00:17:37,020
你所谓的供词
About your supposed confession.

280
00:17:38,090 --> 00:17:40,880
既然你都看过了  我还有什么好补充的呢
What more could I possibly add that you haven't already read?

281
00:17:41,110 --> 00:17:44,420
能看到的是一回事  真相又是一回事
There's what you read, and there's the truth.

282
00:17:45,710 --> 00:17:46,830
我并不觉得羞愧
I'm not ashamed.

283
00:17:47,420 --> 00:17:51,170
休养的时光让我发现了真正的自我
The time away led me to finally realize who I am.

284
00:17:53,210 --> 00:17:56,040
议员知道你的事吗
Does the congressman know about you?

285
00:17:56,650 --> 00:17:58,890
我是说  真的知道吗
I mean... know.

286
00:18:00,270 --> 00:18:02,730
有我的帮助  他会成为下一任众院议长
With my help he's gonna be the next speaker of the House...

287
00:18:02,730 --> 00:18:05,180
我和联邦检察官是法学院同学
I went to law school with the US Attorney.

288
00:18:05,700 --> 00:18:07,160
她等够了
She's tired of waiting.

289
00:18:07,740 --> 00:18:11,860
她明天会签发一张给你的传票
She's issuing a subpoena with your name on it sometime tomorrow.

290
00:18:12,680 --> 00:18:14,590
跟她说实话吧
Tell her what you know.

291
00:18:15,420 --> 00:18:17,900
这样你还有幸存的机会  道格
You have a chance to survive all this, Doug.

292
00:18:23,160 --> 00:18:24,550
塔尔图斯  是吧
Tartus, da?

293
00:18:25,810 --> 00:18:27,650
但舍弃海岸其余的部分
But the rest of the coast...

294
00:18:28,290 --> 00:18:31,440
我们承受得了吗
can we afford to let it go?

295
00:18:33,660 --> 00:18:34,620
再见
Goodbye.

296
00:18:35,070 --> 00:18:36,090
能行
It could work.

297
00:18:36,990 --> 00:18:39,690
佩特罗夫计划把海军基地
Petrov has plans to expand the Naval base

298
00:18:39,760 --> 00:18:41,140
扩建到塔尔图斯港
to the port of Tartus.

299
00:18:41,520 --> 00:18:43,340
他支持叙利亚当局的唯一原因
The only reason he's propping up the regime

300
00:18:43,340 --> 00:18:45,110
就是因为他们控制着海岸
is because they control the coast.

301
00:18:45,120 --> 00:18:46,340
他需要港口
He needs the ports.

302
00:18:47,200 --> 00:18:48,270
只要拿港口挟住他
Force him to fight for those

303
00:18:48,270 --> 00:18:50,180
他就会对叙利亚其余地区放手
and he'll leave the rest of Syria alone.

304
00:18:52,770 --> 00:18:53,650
马克
Mark...

305
00:18:55,850 --> 00:18:57,030
机会来了
the moment is here.

306
00:18:57,030 --> 00:18:58,130
他人在这儿
He's here.

307
00:18:59,040 --> 00:18:59,770
时机不等人啊
It can't wait.

308
00:18:59,770 --> 00:19:01,160
我还是不明白
I still don't understand how

309
00:19:01,160 --> 00:19:03,440
为什么条件还没有谈妥  就已经...
agreements which haven't even been finalized yet...

310
00:19:03,440 --> 00:19:05,730
-不重要  他听到风声了  -谁透的风
- Doesn't matter. He got wind of it. - From who?

311
00:19:06,670 --> 00:19:08,700
重点在于  他是个贪婪的
The point is, is he is a greedy...

312
00:19:08,700 --> 00:19:09,750
王八蛋  没错
Motherfucker, yes.

313
00:19:09,760 --> 00:19:11,860
贪婪的王八蛋总是会察觉
And greedy motherfuckers always find out.

314
00:19:13,330 --> 00:19:14,760
他不达目的不罢休
He's relentless.

315
00:19:17,070 --> 00:19:19,630
我在西北库尔德人区待过两年
I spent two years in the Kurdish northwest,

316
00:19:19,630 --> 00:19:21,900
给东南叛军卖过武器
outfitted rebels in the southeast.

317
00:19:23,020 --> 00:19:26,270
我知道佩特罗夫能打的所有招数
I know every angle Petrov will keep in play.

318
00:19:27,100 --> 00:19:30,510
他对对手的犹疑极其敏感
He has a sixth sense when it comes to hesitation.

319
00:19:33,380 --> 00:19:34,790
如果你需要我参与...
If you need me to be in there...

320
00:19:36,030 --> 00:19:37,960
你就是做不到  是不是
You just can't do it, can you?

321
00:19:39,640 --> 00:19:42,160
-什么  -没什么
- What? - Nothing.

322
00:19:42,490 --> 00:19:45,700
-马克  -你就是不肯放手信任别人
- Mark... - You just can't step back and trust.

323
00:19:46,360 --> 00:19:47,680
我信任你  马克
I trust you, Mark.

324
00:19:48,530 --> 00:19:50,060
但是后座总统
But if the backseat president

325
00:19:50,070 --> 00:19:52,090
想掌权  你就得坐到驾驶席上
is gonna take the wheel, you gotta drive.

326
00:19:55,270 --> 00:19:57,860
你和我孤零零一个人是有原因的  简
There's a reason you and I are alone in the world, Jane.

327
00:20:02,230 --> 00:20:03,460
是  好的
Yes, of course.

328
00:20:06,320 --> 00:20:09,280
-多久没见了  -就好像一辈子
- How long? - A lifetime.

329
00:20:09,880 --> 00:20:12,880
你搬到西部去了吧  能多陪陪儿子了
You moved out west, right? More time with your son.

330
00:20:12,880 --> 00:20:14,590
只要他肯陪我
As much as he'll give me.

331
00:20:14,850 --> 00:20:17,000
-他还喜欢斯坦...  -克莱尔
- And is he still enjoying Stan... - Claire.

332
00:20:17,920 --> 00:20:19,360
总统女士
Madam President,

333
00:20:19,610 --> 00:20:21,970
我们之间用不着来这套虚的
we don't need to exchange pleasantries.

334
00:20:23,770 --> 00:20:27,260
我如今常想  另一种可能是什么样子
These days I tend to think a lot about what might have been.

335
00:20:28,470 --> 00:20:30,000
我想道歉
I'd like to apologize.

336
00:20:31,300 --> 00:20:33,520
-为什么  -我最大的悔恨
- For what? - My one regret.

337
00:20:34,870 --> 00:20:36,780
我应该去加夫尼的
I should've been there in Gaffney.

338
00:20:37,690 --> 00:20:38,720
说真的
Honestly,

339
00:20:39,140 --> 00:20:40,480
我心里一直放不下
it's been haunting me.

340
00:20:40,480 --> 00:20:42,890
有件事该告诉他的
There was something he needed to know.

341
00:20:43,900 --> 00:20:45,230
那是个错误
It was a mistake.

342
00:20:46,850 --> 00:20:49,810
没有让弗兰西斯当国务卿
Overlooking Francis for secretary of state.

343
00:20:49,810 --> 00:20:51,730
-琳达  都过去了  -不对
- Linda, it's water under the bridge. - No.

344
00:20:52,740 --> 00:20:53,740
不对
No.

345
00:20:54,520 --> 00:20:55,980
如果没有当初
If we hadn't,

346
00:20:56,350 --> 00:20:57,390
可就说不准了
I don't know.

347
00:20:57,830 --> 00:20:59,860
也许一切都会不一样了
Maybe everything would have been different.

348
00:21:01,760 --> 00:21:02,810
对谁而言呢
For who?

349
00:21:03,070 --> 00:21:04,280
整个国家
This country.

350
00:21:05,710 --> 00:21:08,270
当然  现在我也没法对他说了
Obviously, there's no way for me to tell him that now.

351
00:21:08,900 --> 00:21:10,930
但至少我还能对你说
The least I can do is tell you.

352
00:21:11,320 --> 00:21:13,190
你不必这样的
There is no need for that.

353
00:21:13,410 --> 00:21:16,250
他那些罪行  你打算怎么撇清关系
How do you expect to separate yourself from his crimes?

354
00:21:17,200 --> 00:21:21,080
虽然我们容忍政治变得如此腐败
As corrupt as these politics we put up with have become...

355
00:21:22,750 --> 00:21:25,500
但反对你的人怎么会不加以利用呢
how can the people against you not use it?

356
00:21:27,640 --> 00:21:29,870
你以为你能清白脱身  克莱尔
You thought you got away with it all, Claire.

357
00:21:30,420 --> 00:21:32,220
但结果还不一定呢
But that remains to be seen.

358
00:21:36,040 --> 00:21:39,320
发生的一切  都是该发生的
Everything happens exactly as it should.

359
00:21:42,120 --> 00:21:43,190
见到你很高兴
Nice seeing you.

360
00:21:57,130 --> 00:21:58,240
你在想什么呢
What are you up to?

361
00:22:01,260 --> 00:22:03,330
我在想生死之事
I'm thinking about mortality.

362
00:22:04,290 --> 00:22:06,460
我想今天好多人都在想这件事
I think a lot of us are doing that today.

363
00:22:07,040 --> 00:22:08,460
一会儿要开个会
We're about to have a meeting.

364
00:22:08,620 --> 00:22:11,000
我参与不了  维克多太了解我了
I can't be a part of it. Viktor knows me all too well.

365
00:22:11,000 --> 00:22:12,180
有我呢
I'm on board.

366
00:22:13,340 --> 00:22:16,460
我知道  克莱尔  我告诉马克不必担心
Claire, I see you. I told Mark not to worry about it.

367
00:22:16,460 --> 00:22:18,220
但我感觉未必...
But I have an inkling that's not necessarily...

368
00:22:18,220 --> 00:22:20,380
少说什么感觉吧  简
Spare me your inkling, Jane.

369
00:22:22,630 --> 00:22:24,530
这个交易是为了你好
This deal is for your own good.

370
00:22:24,530 --> 00:22:26,360
是为了整个地区
It's about the whole region.

371
00:22:26,810 --> 00:22:28,720
事关我们的存在  我们的权威
Our presence. Our authority.

372
00:22:30,230 --> 00:22:32,520
重活交给马克和玛茜去干吧
Mark and Marcy can do the heavy lifting.

373
00:22:35,350 --> 00:22:38,040
今天就帮我阻止战争吧
Help me prevent a war from happening today.

374
00:22:39,070 --> 00:22:41,120
再有任何动荡  所有人都输
Any more instability and everybody loses.

375
00:22:41,130 --> 00:22:42,600
帮我避免这种局面吧
Help me avert that.

376
00:22:45,520 --> 00:22:46,990
我向你保证
I promise you...

377
00:22:48,210 --> 00:22:51,700
我会逐渐瓦解比尔和安奈特·谢泼德的影响力
I will chip away at Bill and Annette Shepherd.

378
00:22:53,640 --> 00:22:56,130
因为要想把他们彻底扳倒
Because the only way to truly take them down

379
00:22:57,810 --> 00:22:59,670
就只能步步为营
is one piece at a time.

380
00:23:04,600 --> 00:23:06,960
你认为凯茜到底发生什么了
What do you think really happened to Cathy?

381
00:23:14,670 --> 00:23:15,770
好吧
Okay.

382
00:23:17,620 --> 00:23:19,230
你大概是运气好吧
I guess you got lucky then.

383
00:23:22,000 --> 00:23:23,500
没人运气那么好
No one is that lucky.

384
00:23:28,040 --> 00:23:30,950
总统愿意对海岸归属不持异议
the President is willing to leave the coast uncontested.

385
00:23:30,950 --> 00:23:33,060
-塔尔图斯港  -已经是我们的了
- Tartus... - That port is already ours.

386
00:23:33,060 --> 00:23:34,430
你们可以继续保留
And will remain so.

387
00:23:34,430 --> 00:23:37,210
我们的军力将远离西海岸
We'll keep our forces away from the entire Western coast.

388
00:23:37,210 --> 00:23:39,770
这样你们就可以自由进出地中海
This will give you unfettered access to the Mediterranean.

389
00:23:39,770 --> 00:23:42,240
-不行  -先生  第六舰队已经出发了
- No. - Sir, the Sixth Fleet is en route.

390
00:23:42,240 --> 00:23:43,860
-不行  -如果你想引发海军对峙的话
- No. - If you want a naval standoff...

391
00:23:43,860 --> 00:23:46,060
打住  咱们都不要装了
No! Let's not pretend.

392
00:23:46,330 --> 00:23:49,790
对你们而言真正重要的是从中取利...
What's really at stake here is your country lining its pockets and...

393
00:23:51,840 --> 00:23:53,120
总统女士
Madam President,

394
00:23:53,630 --> 00:23:54,750
总统先生
Mr. President,

395
00:23:55,120 --> 00:23:57,710
-副总统要求我参会  -格雷森先生
- the vice president asked me to join. - Mr. Grayson...

396
00:23:57,710 --> 00:23:58,740
我代表的是一家
On behalf of a company

397
00:23:58,740 --> 00:24:00,880
-在中东有业务的公司  -你说什么
- with subsidiaries in the Middle East. - Excuse me.

398
00:24:00,890 --> 00:24:03,320
我们希望谈判结果能照顾到我方利益
We want to ensure that we're part of the solution.

399
00:24:03,580 --> 00:24:06,630
这将向全世界发出信号  俄罗斯回来了
This will signal to the world that Russia is back.

400
00:24:06,630 --> 00:24:08,280
-俄罗斯回来了  -副总统先生
- Russia's back? - Mr. Vice President,

401
00:24:08,280 --> 00:24:11,330
正在谈判的一些条件还需要进一步讨论
there are terms being negotiated here that need to be discussed...

402
00:24:11,330 --> 00:24:12,310
天啊
Christ!

403
00:24:13,370 --> 00:24:14,950
要是杜兰特国务卿还在
If Secretary Durant were here,

404
00:24:14,950 --> 00:24:16,890
我们早就过了假模假式的环节
we'd be long past this posturing

405
00:24:16,890 --> 00:24:19,820
-去解决真正问题了  -没错  区域和平
- and dealing with the real question. - Yes, peace in the region.

406
00:24:19,820 --> 00:24:21,750
和平  不是吧
Peace? Really?

407
00:24:22,210 --> 00:24:24,590
你想用和平来决定
You want to use peace to decide

408
00:24:24,760 --> 00:24:28,390
谁来重建这个пиздеть
who will rebuild this pizdets?

409
00:24:28,760 --> 00:24:30,390
我不知道那是什么意思
I don't understand what that means,

410
00:24:30,390 --> 00:24:33,730
-总统先生  -意思是粪坑
- Mr. President. - That means clusterfuck.

411
00:24:33,730 --> 00:24:36,170
先生  维持区域稳定对大家都有好处
Sir, stability in the region helps all of us.

412
00:24:36,320 --> 00:24:38,960
你们想把西部给我  拿走东部
You want to give me the West and take the East?

413
00:24:40,020 --> 00:24:41,530
真是第一次听说
That's a first.

414
00:24:41,830 --> 00:24:43,520
那么我的条件如下
So, here's what I want.

415
00:24:43,740 --> 00:24:45,770
港口我们当然要
The ports, yes, of course.

416
00:24:45,770 --> 00:24:46,950
但我还要求俄罗斯
But I also want Russian

417
00:24:46,950 --> 00:24:50,270
独占所有近海石油和天然气开发
exclusivity on all offshore oil and gas exploration.

418
00:24:50,270 --> 00:24:53,020
-这个得商量一下  -闭嘴吧你
- I think we need to wait. - Shut up.

419
00:24:53,390 --> 00:24:55,250
我们不能进得去
We can't be in a position where we can get in,

420
00:24:55,250 --> 00:24:56,580
却不能把资源带出来
and we can't get our resources out.

421
00:24:56,580 --> 00:24:59,070
历史留给我们的经验  就是
If history has taught us anything, it's that

422
00:24:59,070 --> 00:25:01,220
美国人总有办法全身而退
the Americans always find a way to leave,

423
00:25:01,220 --> 00:25:03,200
无论代价多大
no matter what it costs them.

424
00:25:03,670 --> 00:25:04,640
那么
So...

425
00:25:05,920 --> 00:25:08,730
有什么想法吗  总统女士
thoughts, Madam President?

426
00:25:12,200 --> 00:25:13,290
有话说吗
Anything?

427
00:25:19,080 --> 00:25:21,250
我同意副总统的看法
I concur with the vice president.

428
00:25:28,080 --> 00:25:30,250
看来我们还有很多需要考虑
I believe we have much to consider.

429
00:25:41,770 --> 00:25:44,560
示弱太累了
Playing incompetent is so exhausting.

430
00:25:48,760 --> 00:25:50,240
这一份是总统今晚
Here's a copy of the President's remarks

431
00:25:50,240 --> 00:25:51,990
在国务卿追悼会上的讲话复本
for the secretary's memorial this evening.

432
00:25:51,990 --> 00:25:53,390
我已经有一份了
I already have a copy.

433
00:25:53,650 --> 00:25:55,710
这一份有她在车上做的修改
It includes the changes she made in the car.

434
00:25:55,950 --> 00:25:57,560
好的  谢谢
Right. Thank you.

435
00:26:02,390 --> 00:26:04,270
话说汤姆·耶茨真的失踪了吗
Is it true Tom Yates is missing?

436
00:26:04,480 --> 00:26:05,730
看来是
I believe so.

437
00:26:06,940 --> 00:26:10,480
他真的和白宫里的什么人有一腿吗
Is it true he had an affair with somebody in the White House?

438
00:26:11,250 --> 00:26:12,220
是你吗
Was it you?

439
00:26:12,700 --> 00:26:14,020
什么
Excuse me.

440
00:26:17,280 --> 00:26:18,390
我会看一看的
I'll look through this.

441
00:26:32,150 --> 00:26:33,110
谢谢
Thank you.

442
00:26:37,090 --> 00:26:39,660
-我不喜欢撒谎的人  -我也是
- I don't like liars. - Me neither.

443
00:26:40,020 --> 00:26:41,050
你为什么让我以为...
Why would you let me believe...

444
00:26:41,050 --> 00:26:44,320
你似乎想让我为凯茜的死负责
It seemed like you wanted me to be the one responsible for Cathy.

445
00:26:44,740 --> 00:26:46,810
这可能对你有帮助
That it might be useful to you somehow.

446
00:26:50,220 --> 00:26:53,690
每次我想抽身  就会出什么意外
Every time I plan to quit, something happens.

447
00:26:56,120 --> 00:26:58,680
弗兰西斯一定对我很失望
Francis would certainly be disappointed in me.

448
00:27:02,730 --> 00:27:03,930
不是好习惯
Terrible habit.

449
00:27:05,880 --> 00:27:07,620
不过我戒酒时帮了我的忙
Helped me though when I quit drinking.

450
00:27:10,210 --> 00:27:12,900
不要对联邦检察官开口  道格
Don't say anything to the US attorney, Doug.

451
00:27:12,970 --> 00:27:14,700
她在和谢泼德家族合作
She's working with the Shepherds.

452
00:27:16,110 --> 00:27:17,350
我今晚就赦免你
I pardon you tonight,

453
00:27:17,350 --> 00:27:19,890
她手上你的任何把柄就是我的问题了
and anything else she has will be my problem.

454
00:27:21,960 --> 00:27:23,680
我永远都是你的问题
I'll always be a problem for you.

455
00:27:23,880 --> 00:27:25,680
你还想要我怎样  道格
What do you want from me, Doug?

456
00:27:26,190 --> 00:27:28,250
现在筹码都在你的手上
You're the one with all the leverage here.

457
00:27:29,550 --> 00:27:32,480
科尔议员  我让他跟我一起竞选2020
Congressman Cole. I'll put him on my ticket 2020.

458
00:27:33,330 --> 00:27:35,260
马克一定会走人  我能肯定
Mark won't survive, I'm sure of it.

459
00:27:35,650 --> 00:27:38,140
2024年  布雷特·科尔就是总统
2024, Brett Cole will be the President.

460
00:27:38,230 --> 00:27:40,130
你就能重回白宫
And you will be back in the White House.

461
00:27:42,890 --> 00:27:44,600
我们可以把他推上总统宝座
We can make him president,

462
00:27:45,720 --> 00:27:47,690
就像我们帮弗兰西斯那样
just like we did with Francis.

463
00:27:49,260 --> 00:27:50,930
和科尔搭档的话就是正副不同党了
Cole will mean a split ticket.

464
00:27:51,720 --> 00:27:54,610
也许这正是我们国家最需要的呢
And that might be the very best thing for this country.

465
00:27:58,650 --> 00:28:00,260
那你也得赦免弗兰西斯
Pardon Francis as well.

466
00:28:03,530 --> 00:28:05,430
那我就会被弹劾
If I do that, I could get impeached.

467
00:28:05,630 --> 00:28:06,640
不会
No.

468
00:28:07,530 --> 00:28:10,820
你总能活下来  你已经证明了这一点
You're a survivor. You've proven that much.

469
00:28:12,150 --> 00:28:13,480
赦免他
Pardon him as well.

470
00:28:16,430 --> 00:28:17,830
比尔绝对无法接受
Bill's gonna hate anything

471
00:28:17,830 --> 00:28:19,860
跟克里姆林宫任何形式的合作
even approaching a partnership with the Kremlin.

472
00:28:19,860 --> 00:28:21,810
记仇的是他妹妹
It's his sister who holds a grudge.

473
00:28:21,810 --> 00:28:23,480
但你还是没有选择
But still, you have no choice.

474
00:28:24,550 --> 00:28:28,130
以我的经验  一旦混乱演变成了万劫不复
I mean, in my experience, once the chaos tips into forever,

475
00:28:28,250 --> 00:28:29,200
你也会一无所获
you've got nothing.

476
00:28:29,200 --> 00:28:31,200
而我们离万劫不复就差一点了
And we're very close to forever.

477
00:28:35,390 --> 00:28:36,970
她什么都没说
And she said nothing.

478
00:28:39,560 --> 00:28:41,740
你真的很在意  是不是
It really bothers you, doesn't it?

479
00:28:41,740 --> 00:28:43,370
那些让你看不透的人
When you can't figure a person out.

480
00:28:44,120 --> 00:28:46,960
-尤其是你喜欢的  -天啊  你说什么呢
- Especially when you're attracted. - Oh, my God, what are you...

481
00:28:48,800 --> 00:28:52,000
我和克莱尔·安德伍德没有私情
I am not involved with Claire Underwood.

482
00:28:52,730 --> 00:28:54,770
我说的是安奈特
I'm talking about Annette.

483
00:28:55,850 --> 00:28:58,760
我现在和任何人都没有恋爱关系
I'm not involved with anyone at the moment.

484
00:28:58,770 --> 00:29:01,750
每次看见你们两个在一起  都让我想起往事
Every time I see the both of you together, it brings back memories.

485
00:29:03,640 --> 00:29:05,980
真没想到你也会从幕后走上前台
Never thought you'd step out from behind the scenes.

486
00:29:06,360 --> 00:29:09,030
只要我能为国出力就行  议员
Well, wherever I can do the most good, Congressman.

487
00:29:09,770 --> 00:29:11,360
他可真是一点都没变
He hasn't changed. Not at all.

488
00:29:11,360 --> 00:29:12,730
是好事  也是坏事
Blessing and a curse.

489
00:29:14,150 --> 00:29:16,340
你为我做的一切  我都没忘
I haven't forgotten everything you did for me.

490
00:29:17,430 --> 00:29:19,810
不管有我没我  你都成功进了众议院
Oh, you made it to the House with or without me.

491
00:29:19,900 --> 00:29:21,250
是你带我上的道
You showed me the way.

492
00:29:23,360 --> 00:29:24,320
那么
Well...

493
00:29:25,070 --> 00:29:26,560
我一直想来打个招呼
I've been meaning to say hello,

494
00:29:27,380 --> 00:29:29,860
自从你脱党加入对方之后
ever since you left the party and went to the other side.

495
00:29:32,170 --> 00:29:33,100
简
Jane.

496
00:29:40,320 --> 00:29:42,100
得有十多年没和他说话了
Haven't spoken to him in over a decade.

497
00:29:42,100 --> 00:29:43,150
他知道了
He knows.

498
00:29:43,320 --> 00:29:44,800
他知道我参与其中了
He knows I was involved.

499
00:29:46,040 --> 00:29:47,140
难道你没有吗
Well, weren't you?

500
00:29:49,200 --> 00:29:50,240
你我都有啊
Weren't we?

501
00:29:53,470 --> 00:29:55,260
你上次去我家是什么时候
When's the last time you were in my house?

502
00:29:57,900 --> 00:29:58,860
别
Don't.

503
00:30:01,710 --> 00:30:03,540
马克  我不会再去了
Mark, I'm not going back there.

504
00:30:05,480 --> 00:30:06,440
不是
No, no,

505
00:30:06,440 --> 00:30:09,020
和汤姆·耶茨有私情的是新任新闻发言人
Tom Yates was sleeping with the new press secretary

506
00:30:09,020 --> 00:30:10,310
就在白宫里
in the White House.

507
00:30:16,120 --> 00:30:18,070
他拿东部换西部
He traded the East for the West.

508
00:30:19,130 --> 00:30:22,550
是  所有近海油气开采  先生
Yes, all offshore oil and gas exploration, sir.

509
00:30:25,130 --> 00:30:26,440
他们说我们仍可以进入
They're saying we'll still have access,

510
00:30:26,440 --> 00:30:28,490
但所有通过地中海的航运都会受影响
but all shipping through the Mediterranean will be affected.

511
00:30:28,490 --> 00:30:31,480
而且无法否认  我们将得看他们的脸色
And there's no denying we'll be somewhat at their mercy.

512
00:30:34,830 --> 00:30:36,880
因为根本没时间请示您
Because there wasn't time to consult you.

513
00:30:40,530 --> 00:30:42,010
佩特罗夫加了码
Petrov upped the ante

514
00:30:42,010 --> 00:30:45,050
似乎副总统要让步了
and it looks like the vice president is going to cave.

515
00:30:47,500 --> 00:30:49,700
这个问题不难回答  斯图尔特小姐
It's not a complicated question, Miss Stewart.

516
00:30:50,370 --> 00:30:51,660
你有没有和他上床
Were you sleeping with him?

517
00:30:54,700 --> 00:30:55,670
难道还要我说
Do I need to say

518
00:30:55,670 --> 00:30:58,190
本届政府是在你身上赌了一把吗
this administration has taken a huge chance on you?

519
00:30:58,400 --> 00:31:00,890
-你们到底有没有  -跟你没关系
- Were you sleeping... - It is none of your business.

520
00:31:02,290 --> 00:31:03,670
那就不言自明了
That answers that, then.

521
00:31:06,180 --> 00:31:08,850
这种事正是白宫需要...
This is exactly the kind of thing the White House needs...

522
00:31:11,260 --> 00:31:12,370
避免的
to avoid.

523
00:31:17,000 --> 00:31:18,770
汤姆·耶茨又失踪了
And Tom Yates is missing.

524
00:31:20,270 --> 00:31:22,920
只会让整件事情变得更加可疑
Which only makes the whole story more problematic.

525
00:31:22,920 --> 00:31:24,640
我完全不知道这些流言是哪来的
I have no idea where any of this is coming from.

526
00:31:24,650 --> 00:31:27,740
那我建议你否认的方式更有说服力一些
Well, I suggest you find a more convincing way of denying it.

527
00:31:28,740 --> 00:31:32,610
因为你最大的弱点就是不会撒谎  是不是
Because your inability to lie is a liability, right?

528
00:31:36,720 --> 00:31:38,950
我们的总统又在哪呢
Now, where is our president?

529
00:31:42,880 --> 00:31:45,090
你怎么不告诉他们是我邀请你来的呢
Why didn't you tell them I invited you?

530
00:31:46,600 --> 00:31:47,970
你没有出卖我
You didn't rat me out.

531
00:31:48,110 --> 00:31:50,940
你这口气像黑帮  总统女士
You sound like a gangster, Madam President.

532
00:31:52,880 --> 00:31:54,330
大概是好奇吧
Curiosity, I suppose.

533
00:31:54,330 --> 00:31:56,990
我想看看你怎么做
I wanted to watch you

534
00:31:57,690 --> 00:31:58,730
听听他们怎么说
and hear them.

535
00:32:00,410 --> 00:32:03,290
你的副总统主子太多
Your vice president is serving too many masters.

536
